we go from start to end checking if the next index is increasing or decreasing if it is increasing we buy at current index and sell at next index.


Algorithm:

Step1 : initialize profit = 0
step2 : Start looping the array from i = 1 to n-1:
            if(item[i]>item[i-1] them profit = profit + (item[i-1] - item[i])

step 3: return profit

code:
class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {

        if(prices.length == 0) return 0;
        int profit =0;

        for(int i =1 ; i < prices.length; i++)
        {
            if(prices[i] > prices[i-1])
            {
                profit += prices[i] - prices[i-1];
            }
        }

        return profit;
        
    }
}
